<%- @npm() %> is [ImageMagick](http://www.imagemagick.org) for node, what else is there to say?

    npm install <%= @document.npm.name %>

<img class="hide-on-mobile" src="<%- @image '/imagemagick.png' %>" style="float: right; width: 100px; margin-left: 1em;" />

> ImageMagick is a software suite to create, edit, compose, or convert bitmap images. It can read and write images in a variety of formats (over 100) including DPX, EXR, GIF, JPEG, JPEG-2000, PDF, PNG, Postscript, SVG, and TIFF. Use ImageMagick to resize, flip, mirror, rotate, distort, shear and transform images, adjust image colors, apply various special effects, or draw text, lines, polygons, ellipses and BÃ©zier curves.

The [demo](http://aheckmann.github.io/gm/) page has an interactive playground that shows a tiny fraction of what <%- @npm() %> can do.

    var gm = require('./gm');

    // resize and remove EXIF profile data
    gm('/path/to/my/img.jpg')
      .resize(240, 240)
      .noProfile()
      .write('/path/to/resize.png', function (err) {
        if (!err) console.log('done');
      });

    // annotate an image
    gm('/path/to/my/img.jpg')
      .stroke("#ffffff")
      .drawCircle(10, 10, 20, 10)
      .font("Helvetica.ttf", 12)
      .drawText(30, 20, "GMagick!")
      .write("/path/to/drawing.png", function (err) {
        if (!err) console.log('done');
      });

There are plenty of examples and information on the <%- @npm() %>. Check it out!
